Brazilian Stock Movers: BicBanco Declines; Embraer, Tam Advance

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-08-10T20:39:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/brazilian-stock-movers-bicbanco-falls-embraer-tam-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index climbed 0.5 percent to 51,395.29.  Banco Industrial e Comercial SA (BICB3)  (BICB4 BS) tumbled 5.5
percent to 7 reais. The Sao Paulo-based lender known as BicBanco
reported second-quarter net income of 66.9 million reais ($41.4
million), a 32 percent decline from a year earlier, according to
a regulatory filing. The bank also said it spent 136.5 million
reais in credit-loss provisions in the second-quarter, up from
35.7 million a year before.  Embraer SA (EMBR3)  (EMBR3 BS) rose 2.7 percent to 9.29 reais. The
world’s fourth-largest aircraft maker expects demand for about
545 executive jets in  Brazil , worth $6 billion, within 10 years,
Marco Tulio Pellegrini, the company’s vice-president for
executive aviation, told journalists in Sao Paulo today. In
 China , the company sees demand for 470 executive jets, worth
about $14 billion.  Tam SA (TAMM4)  (TAMM4 BS) gained 4 percent to 25.70 reais. Brazil’s
biggest airline by market value posted an unexpected second-
quarter profit. Net income was 60.3 million reais in the second
quarter, Tam said in a regulatory filing today. The average
estimate from three analysts in a Bloomberg survey was for a
loss of 11.9 million reais.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  